<subSubSection id="413C4CDACFFC8B1A6C5C8449953CF119" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" type="distribution and taxonomic notes">
<paragraph id="A1D24B02539FE4690B4F10C7C2140A48" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">Distribution and taxonomic notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="30619ECCF8B6642AE1377E1D85E87CB0" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">
The nominotypical 
<taxonomicName id="DF38CB7C29E0B6355DC87857662BD28D" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygaena exulans subsp. exulans" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="exulans" subSpecies="exulans">Zygaena exulans exulans</taxonomicName>
is widely distributed throughout the European Alps. While it is acknowledged that variation does occur among some of the populations occurring in this mountain system, we see no justification for recognising any as valid nominal subspecies. When compiling the systematic catalogue (
<bibRefCitation id="40701203EA8304ECD7CDB9C456A751EF" author="Hofmann, A" journalOrPublisher="Harley Books, Colchester" pageId="7" pageNumber="130" title="A systematic Catalogue of the Zygaeninae (Lepidoptera: Zygaenidae)." year="1996">Hofmann and Tremewan 1996</bibRefCitation>
) it was decided that the most rational approach to subspecies in 
<taxonomicName id="30017557669D2B5FE140C8145032E40A" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygaena exulans" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="exulans">Zygaena exulans</taxonomicName>
was to recognise only one subspecies in each major mountain range. 
<bibRefCitation id="4419470F42FAF8F8CAA68D38DB840F64" author="Leraut, P" journalOrPublisher="NAP Editions, Verrieres-le Buisson" pageId="7" pageNumber="130" title="Volume 3: Moths of Europe, Zygaenids, Pyralids 1 and Brachodids." year="2012">Leraut (2012</bibRefCitation>
: 120) reinstated 
<taxonomicName id="35941F43B59884E06FEE8DBC22DF2B95" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygaena exulans subsp. altaretensis" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="exulans" subSpecies="altaretensis">Zygaena exulans altaretensis</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="A9A02398E3FE0961E647F7BB0127EEBD" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygaena exulans subsp. bourgognei" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="exulans" subSpecies="bourgognei">Zygaena exulans bourgognei</taxonomicName>
as valid subspecies without providing justification; both are here formally placed as synonyms (syn. rev.) of the nominotypical 
<taxonomicName id="5ECABA14466308B2C90B53FF4BDACFDA" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygaena exulans subsp. exulans" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="exulans" subSpecies="exulans">Zygaena exulans exulans</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
